repository.name: machinelearning
repository.description: ML.NET is an open source and cross-platform machine learning framework for .NET.

body: That requires the C API supports complex types, which should be a huge work. Because sequences and maps are not the only non-tensor types. Instead of doing them one by one, we should have a clear roadmap first.

There's a model that a user converted to Onnx (see https://github.com/dotnet/machinelearning/issues/1323), which produces a Sequence<Map<int,float>> as an output.  It seems like a valid ONNX model, and therefore should able to run inference on it. Is there a non C API which is running this inference currently?
The python binding is using the C++ API, but C# is using the C API, because it is not possible to access C++ functions through P/Invoke.

Any progress to this? @jignparm 

Loading a model which outputs `Sequence<Map<int,float>>` does not work using the latest C# onnxruntime nuget package (v 0.2.1).
However loading the model using python onnxruntime works fine.

I could really use an implementation of this in the C# onnxruntime.
This functionality is in progress (i.e. the C API supports it now),  and surfacing it in C# is in progress. Should be available next week.

issue.title: read model output from c++

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
Hi, I have a simple scikit-learn model. as in [example](http://onnx.ai/sklearn-onnx/auto_examples/plot_tfidfvectorizer.html) 

With python is everything fine, but I'd like to use model from C API.
For that purpose i used [example](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/docs/C_API.md).
 Everything is fine but I can not get results from my model because of type convertion. 
```c++
/onnxruntime_src/include/onnxruntime/core/framework/ml_value.h:42 T* OrtValue::GetMutable() [with T = onnxruntime::Tensor] onnxruntime::DataTypeImpl::GetType<T>() == type_ was false. N11onnxruntime14TensorTypeBaseE != N11onnxruntime12SequenceTypeISt6vectorISt3mapIlfSt4lessIlESaISt4pairIKlfEEESaIS9_EEEE
```
But I know that onnx supports [Sequence<Map<int,float>>](https://github.com/Microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/156#issuecomment-466512284)
My c++ code looks like this:
```c++
CHECK_STATUS(OrtRun(session, NULL, input_node_names.data(), (const OrtValue* const*)&input_tensor, 1, output_node_names.data(), 1, &output_tensor));
  void ** data;
  CHECK_STATUS(OrtGetTensorMutableData(output_tensor, data));
```
I've seen simmiar [issues](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/1568) but there was no hint. Can anyone help?
